  "key_theorem": "The EML Stochastic Asymmetry Theorem: Stochastic calculus splits sharply by EML depth: Individual paths = EML-\u221e (nowhere differentiable, infinite variation). Forward expectations = EML-0/1/3 (analytic formulas exist). Asymmetry: forward = EML-finite; inverse (parameter recovery) = EML-\u221e always. New finding: characteristic function \u2192 density has \u0394d=2 (char fn = EML-1; density via Fourier inversion = EML-3). This \u0394d=2 is a new type beyond the {0,1,\u221e} seen elsewhere. The Legendre transform is self-dual: EML-2 \u2194 EML-2 with \u0394d=0. Large deviations: rate function = EML-2 (variance-level); LDP probability = EML-1 (exponential). Two different depths from one LDP principle.",
